data.title: Justin Timberlake Biography
data.meta_description: Read all about Justin Timberlake with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

Sang at the Grand Ole Opry when he was 10

Under the name Justin Randall, he performed---and lost---on Star Search in 1992

Appeared as a young Elton John in the flashy songwriter's video for "This Train Don't Stop There Any More

" Launched the William Rast clothing line with friend Trace Ayala in November 2005

Opened the Italian eatery Destino's with Eytan Sugarman in 2006 on Manhattan's Upper East Side

Is an avid golfer and has competed in the AT&T Pebble Beach National Pro-Am

Began hosting the Justin Timberlake Shriners Hospital for Children Open in 2008

Signed on to be the face of Givenchey's new men's fragrance, Play, in 2008

In 2010, began doing ads for their new women's version, Play for Her

Topped GQ's 10 Most Stylish Men in America list in 2009

Received the Big Help Award, which honors philanthropy work, at the 2011 Nickelodeon Kids Choice Awards
